{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":98,"text":"So I have bad news, I have good news,"},{"time":3159,"text":"and I have a task."},{"time":5024,"text":"So the bad news is that we all get sick."},{"time":7967,"text":"I get sick. You get sick."},{"time":10239,"text":"And every one of us gets sick, and the question really is,"},{"time":12781,"text":"how sick do we get? Is it something that kills us?"},{"time":15658,"text":"Is it something that we survive?"},{"time":17003,"text":"Is it something that we can treat?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18931,"text":"And we've gotten sick as long as we've been people."},{"time":22187,"text":"And so we've always looked for reasons to explain why we get sick."},{"time":25673,"text":"And for a long time, it was the gods, right?"},{"time":27630,"text":"The gods are angry with me, or the gods are testing me,"},{"time":30784,"text":"right? Or God, singular, more recently,"},{"time":33200,"text":"is punishing me or judging me."},{"time":35864,"text":"And as long as we've looked for explanations,"},{"time":38544,"text":"we've wound up with something that gets closer and closer to science,"},{"time":42255,"text":"which is hypotheses as to why we get sick,"},{"time":44744,"text":"and as long as we've had hypotheses about why we get sick, we've tried to treat it as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49484,"text":"So this is Avicenna. He wrote a book over a thousand years ago called \"The Canon of Medicine,\""},{"time":53517,"text":"and the rules he laid out for testing medicines"},{"time":55923,"text":"are actually really similar to the rules we have today,"},{"time":57712,"text":"that the disease and the medicine must be the same strength,"},{"time":60657,"text":"the medicine needs to be pure, and in the end we need"},{"time":63054,"text":"to test it in people. And so if you put together these themes"},{"time":66195,"text":"of a narrative or a hypothesis in human testing,"},{"time":70660,"text":"right, you get some beautiful results,"},{"time":73316,"text":"even when we didn't have very good technologies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74758,"text":"This is a guy named Carlos Finlay. He had a hypothesis"},{"time":77820,"text":"that was way outside the box for his time, in the late 1800s."},{"time":80725,"text":"He thought yellow fever was not transmitted by dirty clothing."},{"time":83573,"text":"He thought it was transmitted by mosquitos."},{"time":85999,"text":"And they laughed at him. For 20 years, they called this guy"},{"time":88361,"text":"\"the mosquito man.\" But he ran an experiment in people,"},{"time":91850,"text":"right? He had this hypothesis, and he tested it in people."},{"time":94953,"text":"So he got volunteers to go move to Cuba and live in tents"},{"time":99595,"text":"and be voluntarily infected with yellow fever."},{"time":102630,"text":"So some of the people in some of the tents had dirty clothes"},{"time":105652,"text":"and some of the people were in tents that were full"},{"time":106871,"text":"of mosquitos that had been exposed to yellow fever."},{"time":109127,"text":"And it definitively proved that it wasn't this magic dust"},{"time":112528,"text":"called fomites in your clothes that caused yellow fever."},{"time":115950,"text":"But it wasn't until we tested it in people that we actually knew."},{"time":119326,"text":"And this is what those people signed up for."},{"time":121285,"text":"This is what it looked like to have yellow fever in Cuba"},{"time":124375,"text":"at that time. You suffered in a tent, in the heat, alone,"},{"time":128909,"text":"and you probably died."},{"time":131605,"text":"But people volunteered for this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134822,"text":"And it's not just a cool example of a scientific design"},{"time":138133,"text":"of experiment in theory. They also did this beautiful thing."},{"time":141046,"text":"They signed this document, and it's called an informed consent document."},{"time":144965,"text":"And informed consent is an idea that we should be"},{"time":147478,"text":"very proud of as a society, right? It's something that"},{"time":149704,"text":"separates us from the Nazis at Nuremberg,"},{"time":152470,"text":"enforced medical experimentation. It's the idea"},{"time":155345,"text":"that agreement to join a study without understanding isn't agreement."},{"time":159133,"text":"It's something that protects us from harm, from hucksters,"},{"time":163242,"text":"from people that would try to hoodwink us into a clinical"},{"time":166095,"text":"study that we don't understand, or that we don't agree to."},{"time":169847,"text":"And so you put together the thread of narrative hypothesis,"},{"time":174176,"text":"experimentation in humans, and informed consent,"},{"time":176773,"text":"and you get what we call clinical study, and it's how we do"},{"time":179438,"text":"the vast majority of medical work. It doesn't really matter"},{"time":182453,"text":"if you're in the north, the south, the east, the west."},{"time":184795,"text":"Clinical studies form the basis of how we investigate,"},{"time":188908,"text":"so if we're going to look at a new drug, right,"},{"time":190767,"text":"we test it in people, we draw blood, we do experiments,"},{"time":193765,"text":"and we gain consent for that study, to make sure"},{"time":196094,"text":"that we're not screwing people over as part of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198743,"text":"But the world is changing around the clinical study,"},{"time":202407,"text":"which has been fairly well established for tens of years"},{"time":205773,"text":"if not 50 to 100 years."},{"time":207673,"text":"So now we're able to gather data about our genomes,"},{"time":210724,"text":"but, as we saw earlier, our genomes aren't dispositive."},{"time":213584,"text":"We're able to gather information about our environment."},{"time":216350,"text":"And more importantly, we're able to gather information"},{"time":218260,"text":"about our choices, because it turns out that what we think of"},{"time":221100,"text":"as our health is more like the interaction of our bodies,"},{"time":223820,"text":"our genomes, our choices and our environment."},{"time":227469,"text":"And the clinical methods that we've got aren't very good"},{"time":230213,"text":"at studying that because they are based on the idea"},{"time":232845,"text":"of person-to-person interaction. You interact"},{"time":234759,"text":"with your doctor and you get enrolled in the study."},{"time":236854,"text":"So this is my grandfather. I actually never met him,"},{"time":239469,"text":"but he's holding my mom, and his genes are in me, right?"},{"time":243264,"text":"His choices ran through to me. He was a smoker,"},{"time":246155,"text":"like most people were. This is my son."},{"time":248739,"text":"So my grandfather's genes go all the way through to him,"},{"time":252181,"text":"and my choices are going to affect his health."},{"time":254733,"text":"The technology between these two pictures"},{"time":257427,"text":"cannot be more different, but the methodology"},{"time":261100,"text":"for clinical studies has not radically changed over that time period."},{"time":265224,"text":"We just have better statistics."},{"time":267892,"text":"The way we gain informed consent was formed in large part"},{"time":271344,"text":"after World War II, around the time that picture was taken."},{"time":273935,"text":"That was 70 years ago, and the way we gain informed consent,"},{"time":277869,"text":"this tool that was created to protect us from harm,"},{"time":280746,"text":"now creates silos. So the data that we collect"},{"time":284412,"text":"for prostate cancer or for Alzheimer's trials"},{"time":287138,"text":"goes into silos where it can only be used"},{"time":289753,"text":"for prostate cancer or for Alzheimer's research."},{"time":292977,"text":"Right? It can't be networked. It can't be integrated."},{"time":295871,"text":"It cannot be used by people who aren't credentialed."},{"time":299404,"text":"So a physicist can't get access to it without filing paperwork."},{"time":302357,"text":"A computer scientist can't get access to it without filing paperwork."},{"time":305425,"text":"Computer scientists aren't patient. They don't file paperwork."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309568,"text":"And this is an accident. These are tools that we created"},{"time":313554,"text":"to protect us from harm, but what they're doing"},{"time":316821,"text":"is protecting us from innovation now."},{"time":319351,"text":"And that wasn't the goal. It wasn't the point. Right?"},{"time":322616,"text":"It's a side effect, if you will, of a power we created"},{"time":325315,"text":"to take us for good."},{"time":327674,"text":"And so if you think about it, the depressing thing is that"},{"time":330818,"text":"Facebook would never make a change to something"},{"time":332951,"text":"as important as an advertising algorithm"},{"time":335522,"text":"with a sample size as small as a Phase III clinical trial."},{"time":339933,"text":"We cannot take the information from past trials"},{"time":343595,"text":"and put them together to form statistically significant samples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347749,"text":"And that sucks, right? So 45 percent of men develop"},{"time":351233,"text":"cancer. Thirty-eight percent of women develop cancer."},{"time":354330,"text":"One in four men dies of cancer."},{"time":356674,"text":"One in five women dies of cancer, at least in the United States."},{"time":360230,"text":"And three out of the four drugs we give you"},{"time":362458,"text":"if you get cancer fail. And this is personal to me."},{"time":365971,"text":"My sister is a cancer survivor."},{"time":367934,"text":"My mother-in-law is a cancer survivor. Cancer sucks."},{"time":371523,"text":"And when you have it, you don't have a lot of privacy"},{"time":373713,"text":"in the hospital. You're naked the vast majority of the time."},{"time":377200,"text":"People you don't know come in and look at you and poke you and prod you,"},{"time":380895,"text":"and when I tell cancer survivors that this tool we created"},{"time":384336,"text":"to protect them is actually preventing their data from being used,"},{"time":387434,"text":"especially when only three to four percent of people"},{"time":389484,"text":"who have cancer ever even sign up for a clinical study,"},{"time":392282,"text":"their reaction is not, \"Thank you, God, for protecting my privacy.\""},{"time":395840,"text":"It's outrage"},{"time":398537,"text":"that we have this information and we can't use it."},{"time":400662,"text":"And it's an accident."},{"time":403138,"text":"So the cost in blood and treasure of this is enormous."},{"time":406193,"text":"Two hundred and twenty-six billion a year is spent on cancer in the United States."},{"time":409848,"text":"Fifteen hundred people a day die in the United States."},{"time":413067,"text":"And it's getting worse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415640,"text":"So the good news is that some things have changed,"},{"time":418622,"text":"and the most important thing that's changed"},{"time":420175,"text":"is that we can now measure ourselves in ways"},{"time":422513,"text":"that used to be the dominion of the health system."},{"time":425571,"text":"So a lot of people talk about it as digital exhaust."},{"time":427729,"text":"I like to think of it as the dust that runs along behind my kid."},{"time":430771,"text":"We can reach back and grab that dust,"},{"time":433147,"text":"and we can learn a lot about health from it, so if our choices"},{"time":435561,"text":"are part of our health, what we eat is a really important"},{"time":438241,"text":"aspect of our health. So you can do something very simple"},{"time":440930,"text":"and basic and take a picture of your food,"},{"time":442887,"text":"and if enough people do that, we can learn a lot about"},{"time":445771,"text":"how our food affects our health."},{"time":447196,"text":"One interesting thing that came out of this — this is an app for iPhones called The Eatery —"},{"time":451712,"text":"is that we think our pizza is significantly healthier"},{"time":454202,"text":"than other people's pizza is. Okay? (Laughter)"},{"time":457640,"text":"And it seems like a trivial result, but this is the sort of research"},{"time":461248,"text":"that used to take the health system years"},{"time":463562,"text":"and hundreds of thousands of dollars to accomplish."},{"time":465855,"text":"It was done in five months by a startup company of a couple of people."},{"time":469579,"text":"I don't have any financial interest in it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472203,"text":"But more nontrivially, we can get our genotypes done,"},{"time":474899,"text":"and although our genotypes aren't dispositive, they give us clues."},{"time":477717,"text":"So I could show you mine. It's just A's, T's, C's and G's."},{"time":480523,"text":"This is the interpretation of it. As you can see,"},{"time":482755,"text":"I carry a 32 percent risk of prostate cancer,"},{"time":485355,"text":"22 percent risk of psoriasis and a 14 percent risk of Alzheimer's disease."},{"time":489578,"text":"So that means, if you're a geneticist, you're freaking out,"},{"time":492185,"text":"going, \"Oh my God, you told everyone you carry the ApoE E4 allele. What's wrong with you?\""},{"time":496219,"text":"Right? When I got these results, I started talking to doctors,"},{"time":499907,"text":"and they told me not to tell anyone, and my reaction is,"},{"time":502316,"text":"\"Is that going to help anyone cure me when I get the disease?\""},{"time":505604,"text":"And no one could tell me yes."},{"time":508668,"text":"And I live in a web world where, when you share things,"},{"time":511474,"text":"beautiful stuff happens, not bad stuff."},{"time":514184,"text":"So I started putting this in my slide decks,"},{"time":516084,"text":"and I got even more obnoxious, and I went to my doctor,"},{"time":518545,"text":"and I said, \"I'd like to actually get my bloodwork."},{"time":520527,"text":"Please give me back my data.\" So this is my most recent bloodwork."},{"time":523317,"text":"As you can see, I have high cholesterol."},{"time":525686,"text":"I have particularly high bad cholesterol, and I have some"},{"time":528437,"text":"bad liver numbers, but those are because we had a dinner party with a lot of good wine"},{"time":531440,"text":"the night before we ran the test. (Laughter)"},{"time":534149,"text":"Right. But look at how non-computable this information is."},{"time":538562,"text":"This is like the photograph of my granddad holding my mom"},{"time":541536,"text":"from a data perspective, and I had to go into the system"},{"time":545135,"text":"and get it out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547297,"text":"So the thing that I'm proposing we do here"},{"time":550579,"text":"is that we reach behind us and we grab the dust,"},{"time":552995,"text":"that we reach into our bodies and we grab the genotype,"},{"time":555973,"text":"and we reach into the medical system and we grab our records,"},{"time":558674,"text":"and we use it to build something together, which is a commons."},{"time":562114,"text":"And there's been a lot of talk about commonses, right,"},{"time":565258,"text":"here, there, everywhere, right. A commons is nothing more"},{"time":568206,"text":"than a public good that we build out of private goods."},{"time":571134,"text":"We do it voluntarily, and we do it through standardized"},{"time":573903,"text":"legal tools. We do it through standardized technologies."},{"time":576703,"text":"Right. That's all a commons is. It's something that we build"},{"time":579974,"text":"together because we think it's important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582494,"text":"And a commons of data is something that's really unique,"},{"time":585126,"text":"because we make it from our own data. And although"},{"time":587994,"text":"a lot of people like privacy as their methodology of control"},{"time":590281,"text":"around data, and obsess around privacy, at least"},{"time":592536,"text":"some of us really like to share as a form of control,"},{"time":595584,"text":"and what's remarkable about digital commonses"},{"time":597937,"text":"is you don't need a big percentage if your sample size is big enough"},{"time":601469,"text":"to generate something massive and beautiful."},{"time":603980,"text":"So not that many programmers write free software,"},{"time":606538,"text":"but we have the Apache web server."},{"time":608873,"text":"Not that many people who read Wikipedia edit,"},{"time":611570,"text":"but it works. So as long as some people like to share"},{"time":615579,"text":"as their form of control, we can build a commons, as long as we can get the information out."},{"time":619323,"text":"And in biology, the numbers are even better."},{"time":621699,"text":"So Vanderbilt ran a study asking people, we'd like to take"},{"time":624251,"text":"your biosamples, your blood, and share them in a biobank,"},{"time":627573,"text":"and only five percent of the people opted out."},{"time":629945,"text":"I'm from Tennessee. It's not the most science-positive state"},{"time":633037,"text":"in the United States of America. (Laughter)"},{"time":636076,"text":"But only five percent of the people wanted out."},{"time":638454,"text":"So people like to share, if you give them the opportunity and the choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642477,"text":"And the reason that I got obsessed with this, besides the obvious family aspects,"},{"time":646960,"text":"is that I spend a lot of time around mathematicians,"},{"time":650233,"text":"and mathematicians are drawn to places where there's a lot of data"},{"time":653147,"text":"because they can use it to tease signals out of noise."},{"time":656090,"text":"And those correlations that they can tease out, they're not"},{"time":659058,"text":"necessarily causal agents, but math, in this day and age,"},{"time":662930,"text":"is like a giant set of power tools"},{"time":665290,"text":"that we're leaving on the floor, not plugged in in health,"},{"time":669165,"text":"while we use hand saws."},{"time":671477,"text":"If we have a lot of shared genotypes, and a lot of shared"},{"time":675915,"text":"outcomes, and a lot of shared lifestyle choices,"},{"time":678663,"text":"and a lot of shared environmental information, we can start"},{"time":681439,"text":"to tease out the correlations between subtle variations"},{"time":684335,"text":"in people, the choices they make and the health that they create as a result of those choices,"},{"time":689646,"text":"and there's open-source infrastructure to do all of this."},{"time":692132,"text":"Sage Bionetworks is a nonprofit that's built a giant math system"},{"time":695226,"text":"that's waiting for data, but there isn't any."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699798,"text":"So that's what I do. I've actually started what we think is"},{"time":703686,"text":"the world's first fully digital, fully self-contributed,"},{"time":707624,"text":"unlimited in scope, global in participation, ethically approved"},{"time":712659,"text":"clinical research study where you contribute the data."},{"time":716314,"text":"So if you reach behind yourself and you grab the dust,"},{"time":718520,"text":"if you reach into your body and grab your genome,"},{"time":721146,"text":"if you reach into the medical system and somehow extract your medical record,"},{"time":724193,"text":"you can actually go through an online informed consent process --"},{"time":727516,"text":"because the donation to the commons must be voluntary"},{"time":730162,"text":"and it must be informed -- and you can actually upload"},{"time":732955,"text":"your information and have it syndicated to the"},{"time":735547,"text":"mathematicians who will do this sort of big data research,"},{"time":738643,"text":"and the goal is to get 100,000 in the first year"},{"time":741499,"text":"and a million in the first five years so that we have"},{"time":743857,"text":"a statistically significant cohort that you can use to take"},{"time":747691,"text":"smaller sample sizes from traditional research"},{"time":750113,"text":"and map it against,"},{"time":751712,"text":"so that you can use it to tease out those subtle correlations"},{"time":754634,"text":"between the variations that make us unique"},{"time":757163,"text":"and the kinds of health that we need to move forward as a society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761187,"text":"And I've spent a lot of time around other commons."},{"time":764211,"text":"I've been around the early web. I've been around"},{"time":766891,"text":"the early creative commons world, and there's four things"},{"time":769499,"text":"that all of these share, which is, they're all really simple."},{"time":772853,"text":"And so if you were to go to the website and enroll in this study,"},{"time":775580,"text":"you're not going to see something complicated."},{"time":777835,"text":"But it's not simplistic. These things are weak intentionally,"},{"time":782884,"text":"right, because you can always add power and control to a system,"},{"time":785907,"text":"but it's very difficult to remove those things if you put them in at the beginning,"},{"time":789871,"text":"and so being simple doesn't mean being simplistic,"},{"time":792416,"text":"and being weak doesn't mean weakness."},{"time":794600,"text":"Those are strengths in the system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796951,"text":"And open doesn't mean that there's no money."},{"time":799616,"text":"Closed systems, corporations, make a lot of money"},{"time":802636,"text":"on the open web, and they're one of the reasons why the open web lives"},{"time":806175,"text":"is that corporations have a vested interest in the openness"},{"time":809002,"text":"of the system."},{"time":811336,"text":"And so all of these things are part of the clinical study that we've created,"},{"time":815130,"text":"so you can actually come in, all you have to be is 14 years old,"},{"time":818559,"text":"willing to sign a contract that says I'm not going to be a jerk,"},{"time":820586,"text":"basically, and you're in."},{"time":823251,"text":"You can start analyzing the data."},{"time":824824,"text":"You do have to solve a CAPTCHA as well. (Laughter)"},{"time":828983,"text":"And if you'd like to build corporate structures on top of it,"},{"time":832564,"text":"that's okay too. That's all in the consent,"},{"time":835710,"text":"so if you don't like those terms, you don't come in."},{"time":838274,"text":"It's very much the design principles of a commons"},{"time":841366,"text":"that we're trying to bring to health data."},{"time":843960,"text":"And the other thing about these systems is that it only takes"},{"time":846939,"text":"a small number of really unreasonable people working together"},{"time":850118,"text":"to create them. It didn't take that many people"},{"time":853300,"text":"to make Wikipedia Wikipedia, or to keep it Wikipedia."},{"time":856772,"text":"And we're not supposed to be unreasonable in health,"},{"time":858840,"text":"and so I hate this word \"patient.\""},{"time":861116,"text":"I don't like being patient when systems are broken,"},{"time":864283,"text":"and health care is broken."},{"time":866910,"text":"I'm not talking about the politics of health care, I'm talking about the way we scientifically approach health care."},{"time":871074,"text":"So I don't want to be patient. And the task I'm giving to you"},{"time":874344,"text":"is to not be patient. So I'd like you to actually try,"},{"time":877390,"text":"when you go home, to get your data."},{"time":880107,"text":"You'll be shocked and offended and, I would bet, outraged,"},{"time":882824,"text":"at how hard it is to get it."},{"time":885700,"text":"But it's a challenge that I hope you'll take,"},{"time":888319,"text":"and maybe you'll share it. Maybe you won't."},{"time":890780,"text":"If you don't have anyone in your family who's sick,"},{"time":892224,"text":"maybe you wouldn't be unreasonable. But if you do,"},{"time":895217,"text":"or if you've been sick, then maybe you would."},{"time":897424,"text":"And we're going to be able to do an experiment in the next several months"},{"time":900512,"text":"that lets us know exactly how many unreasonable people are out there."},{"time":903669,"text":"So this is the Athena Breast Health Network. It's a study"},{"time":905791,"text":"of 150,000 women in California, and they're going to"},{"time":909609,"text":"return all the data to the participants of the study"},{"time":912327,"text":"in a computable form, with one-clickability to load it into"},{"time":915473,"text":"the study that I've put together. So we'll know exactly"},{"time":918089,"text":"how many people are willing to be unreasonable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":920393,"text":"So what I'd end [with] is,"},{"time":922777,"text":"the most beautiful thing I've learned since I quit my job"},{"time":926097,"text":"almost a year ago to do this, is that it really doesn't take"},{"time":929480,"text":"very many of us to achieve spectacular results."},{"time":933288,"text":"You just have to be willing to be unreasonable,"},{"time":936000,"text":"and the risk we're running is not the risk those 14 men"},{"time":938331,"text":"who got yellow fever ran. Right?"},{"time":940199,"text":"It's to be naked, digitally, in public. So you know more"},{"time":943060,"text":"about me and my health than I know about you. It's asymmetric now."},{"time":946493,"text":"And being naked and alone can be terrifying."},{"time":950123,"text":"But to be naked in a group, voluntarily, can be quite beautiful."},{"time":954590,"text":"And so it doesn't take all of us."},{"time":956478,"text":"It just takes all of some of us. Thank you."},{"time":959484,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}